        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 10:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is: He is (1) to receive a hundredfold now, in the period prior to the manifestation of the Messiah, namely, a hundred times as many houses, brothers, etc.; and (2) to receive in the coming period (“jam in adventu est,” Bengel), after the Parousia, the everlasting life of the Messiah’s kingdom.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "plurals",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which express the number a hundred, plainly show that the promised compensation in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καιρὸς οὗτος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is not to be understood literally, but generally, of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "very abundant compensation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Nevertheless, the delicate feeling of Jesus has not said ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "γυναῖκας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " also. So much the more clumsy was Julian’s scoff (see Theophylact) that the Christians were, moreover, to receive a hundred wives! The promise was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "realized",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
